%% Per-decision-cycle data flow (sequence) — render at https://mermaid.live
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant WG as Workload Gen
    participant K as Kafka
    participant EN as Placement Engine (Spark)
    participant ML as MLlib model
    participant ED as Edge (Redis)
    participant CL as Cloud (HDFS)
    participant DB as Dashboard

    loop every decision_interval
        WG->>K: publish access events (Zipfian)
        EN->>K: poll micro-batch
        EN->>EN: Spark windowed aggregation (counts, recency)
        EN->>EN: update EMA baseline
        EN->>ML: add labelled samples, (re)train periodically
        ML-->>EN: predicted next-window demand
        EN->>EN: pick top-K hot set (EMA vs ML)
        EN->>CL: read bytes of newly-hot datasets
        EN->>ED: PROMOTE hot, EVICT cold (migrations)
        Note over EN,ED: serve path: HIT=Redis(~2ms), MISS=HDFS(+80ms)
        EN->>ED: publish metrics snapshot
        DB->>ED: read metrics + render charts
    end
